Format text to 75 columns
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Start vim with the file you want to format.
2. Make sure you have "par" installed. If not: sudo apt-get install par.
3. In vim enter :set formatprg=par \75j
4. Select the text you want to format. Shift+V and } to go to the end of the
   line.
5. Use the gq command.
6. Also you can use par from the shell: cat <yourfile> | par 60j
   where 60 is the number of columns and j is justified.

